    dc:title "Taxonomic revision of the parrot snake Leptophis ahaetulla (Serpentes, Colubridae)" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6631020>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6631038>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6630989>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6631042>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6631040> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6631020>
    dc:description "FIGURE 22. Sulcate (left) and asulcate (right) sides of the hemipenes of Leptophis marginatus (FML 1624) from Puerto Pilcomayo, departament of Pilcomayo, Formosa Province, Argentina (A-B); L. urostictus (AMNH 109753) from Guanguí stream, department of Cauca, Colombia (C-D); L. occidentalis (ANSP 32397), from province of Limón, Costa Rica (E-F); and L. praestans (KU 55716) from El Petén, Guatemala (G-H) sides. Note the first row of moderate-sized spines in the first two species, and the enlarged spines in the latter two species. Scale bars = 0.5 cm. Photos by N.R. Albuquerque." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6631020/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6631038>
    dc:description "FIGURE 30. Color pattern and color tones of Leptophis praestans: UTA 12685 from Blue Creek Village, district of Toledo, Belize. Arrow indicating yellow chevron-shaped marks on the interstitial skin. Photo by W.W. Lamar, courtesy of J.A. Campbell." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6631038/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6630989>
    dc:description "FIGURE 8. Distribution of Leptophis bocourti, L. coeruleodorsus, L. occidentalis, L. praestans, and L. urostictus based upon the material examined." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6630989/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6631042>
    dc:description "FIGURE 32. Color pattern and color tones of Leptophis praestans: Profile view of the UMMZ 74851 from El Petén, Guatemala. This juvenile specimen retains traces of a postocular stripe (indicated by the arrow) reduced to black margin on eighth and ninth supralabials, occupying lower one-third of anterior temporal and lower one-third of posterior temporal, suggesting a possible ontogenetic change in L. praestans. This condition is absent in adult specimens. Scale bar = 0.5 cm. Photo by N.R. Albuquerque." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6631042/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6631040>
    dc:description "FIGURE 31. Color pattern and color tones of Leptophis praestans: Male syntype USNM 6754 (paralectotype by designation), SVL 1748 mm (incomplete tail). General view (A). Although faded, the black keels on the V–VII and IX–XI dorsal scale rows and the chevron-shaped markings (indicated by the arrow) are still evident. (B) Profile view. Note the absence of postocular stripe, a condition typical of adult specimens. Scale bar = 0.5 cm. Photos by N.R. Albuquerque." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6631040/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

